protecting the city were breached,

00:30:25.060 --> 00:30:28.830
flooding much of New Orleans.

00:30:28.830 --> 00:30:34.180
In the aftermath the likes of
Dan Rather were very extravagant

00:30:34.180 --> 00:30:38.400
in saying that this was
a high heroic moment

00:30:38.400 --> 00:30:39.830
in American journalism.

00:30:39.830 --> 00:30:42.730
He called it one of the
quintessential great moments

00:30:42.730 --> 00:30:45.460
in television news
ranking, right up there

00:30:45.460 --> 00:30:48.660
with the Nixon/Kennedy debates,
the Kennedy assassination,

00:30:48.660 --> 00:30:51.520 position:56%
the Watergate coverage, you name it.

00:30:51.520 --> 00:30:54.710
It was a landmark, Dan Rather said.

00:30:54.710 --> 00:30:59.080
And the media narrative about
Hurricane Katrina was much

00:30:59.080 --> 00:31:01.990
like that, that this
was a memorable moment

00:31:01.990 --> 00:31:08.820 position:56%
in which the media found their voice
and were able to confront and stand

00:31:08.820 --> 00:31:13.740
up to public officials,
local, state, and federal,

00:31:13.740 --> 00:31:18.920
holding them accountable for what
was a pretty muddled response.

00:31:18.920 --> 00:31:22.300
Especially by federal and local
authorities in New Orleans

00:31:22.300 --> 00:31:24.370
in the aftermath of the hurricane.

00:31:24.370 --> 00:31:28.710
The reality, though,
was quite different.

00:31:28.710 --> 00:31:32.040
The reality of the
reporting was quite different.

00:31:32.040 --> 00:31:35.610
There was no high heroic
moment in American journalism.

00:31:35.610 --> 00:31:38.820
And in important respects
the coverage

00:31:38.820 --> 00:31:44.410
of Hurricane Katrina's aftermath
was badly flawed and exaggerated.

00:31:44.410 --> 00:31:46.820
They got it wrong.

00:31:46.820 --> 00:31:49.380
Crucial details.

00:31:49.380 --> 00:31:51.490
Journalists were in error.

00:31:51.490 --> 00:31:56.920 position:56%
They described scenes of apocalyptic
horror and mayhem, and lawlessness

00:31:56.920 --> 00:32:03.160
that the storm supposedly had
unleashed across New Orleans.

00:32:03.160 --> 00:32:07.370
They told of snipers
firing at medical personnel,

00:32:07.370 --> 00:32:11.270
snipers firing at helicopters.

00:32:11.270 --> 00:32:16.560
They told of bodies being stacked
up like cordwood in the Superdome

00:32:16.560 --> 00:32:19.030
and convention center
where people sought refuge

00:32:19.030 --> 00:32:21.680
from the storm's after effects.

00:32:21.680 --> 00:32:26.410
They talked about roving
gangs preying on tourists,

00:32:26.410 --> 00:32:31.450
terrorizing people who took
refuge in the Superdome.

00:32:31.450 --> 00:32:35.420
They said children were the
victims of sexual assault,

00:32:35.420 --> 00:32:40.240
how one seven-year-old was raped
