You know, it's on the
cusp of plausibility.

00:42:16.450 --> 00:42:18.840
On the cusp of plausibility.

00:42:18.840 --> 00:42:20.410
So let me just recap.

00:42:20.410 --> 00:42:24.740
Remember that early accounts
of disasters often are untrue.

00:42:24.740 --> 00:42:26.440
There are errors there.

00:42:26.440 --> 00:42:30.530
And to be wary of those.

00:42:30.530 --> 00:42:33.090
Hone that ability to
develop the sniff test.

00:42:33.090 --> 00:42:36.330
If stories don't seem to be quite
right, you're probably right.

00:42:36.330 --> 00:42:40.830
Applying your logic, applying
your experience, saying, "Hmm.

00:42:40.830 --> 00:42:43.120
Maybe it's not quite true."

00:42:43.120 --> 00:42:45.690
The sniff test.

00:42:45.690 --> 00:42:51.030 position:56%
Be wary of stories based exclusively
or largely on anonymous sources.

00:42:51.030 --> 00:42:52.460 position:56%
