01:01:19.580 --> 01:01:23.810
and has been used as
an example of, "Okay.

01:01:23.810 --> 01:01:29.410
If Jefferson smoked hemp, then
why lot legalize marijuana?"

01:01:29.410 --> 01:01:34.380 position:56%
In fact, Gary Johnson, the
libertarian candidate for president,

01:01:34.380 --> 01:01:37.990
not this most recent
time, but his -- 2012?

01:01:37.990 --> 01:01:43.710
In 2012 he was on a talk show
and invoked this quotation.

01:01:43.710 --> 01:01:46.380
Didn't Jefferson say that
he liked to smoke hemp?

01:01:46.380 --> 01:01:50.520
And as an example of, okay,
third president and one

01:01:50.520 --> 01:01:52.830
of the founding fathers and
author of the "Declaration

01:01:52.830 --> 01:01:54.510
of Independence" smoked hemp.

01:01:54.510 --> 01:01:56.520 position:56%
Then it's good enough for us, right?

01:01:56.520 --> 01:02:00.200
So there is an agenda behind
that, and it's one of these quotes

01:02:00.200 --> 01:02:02.080
that you just find on
Twitter all the time.

01:02:02.080 --> 01:02:07.340
There is no, no attempt to knock
it down or to say, "This is bogus."

01:02:07.340 --> 01:02:09.980
But it is quite clearly.

01:02:09.980 --> 01:02:12.060
And there are many others.

01:02:12.060 --> 01:02:19.240
I mean great men and women are
often -- who are deceased are --

01:02:19.240 --> 01:02:21.050
Great quotes are put
in to their mouths

01:02:21.050 --> 01:02:22.810
and they never ever
said these things.

01:02:22.810 --> 01:02:27.930
And Einstein, Benjamin
Franklin, you know, you name it,

01:02:27.930 --> 01:02:31.380
George Washington, there are
lots of phony quotes attributed

01:02:31.380 --> 01:02:33.090
to these famous people of the past.

01:02:33.090 --> 01:02:36.130
And that's one way these famous
quotes or these bogus quotes live

01:02:36.130 --> 01:02:39.190
on by attachment to famous people.

01:02:39.190 --> 01:02:43.190
&gt;&gt; Speaker 6: One case with
